                            <comment id="14543554" author="njiang" created="Thu, 14 May 2015 12:14:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied the patch into camel master, camel-2.14.x and camel-2.15.x branches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14543642" author="matihost" created="Thu, 14 May 2015 13:05:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks better, but I&apos;m wondering still about &quot;Content-Encoding&quot; header.&lt;br/&gt;
It is not included  in HttpHeaderFilterStrategy.&lt;br/&gt;
Could you add also some test for that?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PS. Thanks for really fast attention.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14544774" author="njiang" created="Fri, 15 May 2015 01:58:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Mateusz, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You are right, I made a mistake to use the HttpHeaderFilterStrategy directly.&lt;br/&gt;
As this HttpHeaderFilter doesn&apos;t filter all http related protocol and it also filter the Camel related headers. &lt;br/&gt;
I will commit a quick fix for it by apply a custom HttpHeaderFilterStrategy to use.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Willem&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14544784" author="njiang" created="Fri, 15 May 2015 02:09:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just found camel-http, camel-http4, camel-ahc have the same issue here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
